'''Sir Chris N. Banks''' [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (born 1959) is a British businessman.

Sir Chris Banks graduated from [[Birmingham University]] with a BA degree in [[Latin]] and [[French language|French]] 1980. He graduated from [[Aston University]] with an [[MBA]] degree in 1981.<ref>{{cite web|author=Shibley Rahman |url=http://www.businessbecause.com/news/mba-entrepreneurs/876/chris-banks-from-latin-to-coca-cola |title=Chris Banks, From Latin To Coca Cola |publisher=Businessbecause.com |date=2011-06-24 |accessdate=2015-04-01}}</ref>

Sir Chris was Managing Director of [[Coca-Cola]] Great Britain from 1997 to 2001. He was Chairman of the [[Learning and Skills Council]], Deputy Chair of the National Employment Panel, and a Commissioner for Women and Work. He is a founder of the Independent College Partnership. In 2011 he completed an independent review into fees and co-funding in Further Education. He is the Chair of the Public Chairs’ Forum (PCF). He is Chair of [[Directgov]]. He is the Deputy [[Pro-Chancellor]] of Birmingham University.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/university/governance/Council/membership/chris-banks.aspx |title=Dr Chris Banks - University of Birmingham |publisher=Birmingham.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-04-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150214222527/http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/university/governance/Council/membership/chris-banks.aspx |archivedate=2015-02-14 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://alumni-web-01.aston.ac.uk/alist/details/30/chris-banks |title=Chris Banks &#124; The A List |publisher=Alumni-web-01.aston.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.national-training.com/events/conferences/eec2010/ChrisNBanksSpeakerProfile.php |title=Chris N Banks Speaker Profile |publisher=National-training.com |date=2010-09-27 |accessdate=2015-04-01}}</ref>

In 2004 Sir Chris was named [[Ernst & Young]] Entrepreneur of the Year (Consumer Products, London).Sir Chris was appointed a [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] (CBE) in 2003 for services to young people and the unemployed{{Citation needed|date=September 2016}}. Sir Chris was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of the University (DUniv) by the [[University of Birmingham]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/news/latest/2012/12/3-Dec-Honorary-Graduands-for-December-2012-.aspx |title=Honorary Graduands for December 2012 |publisher=Birmingham.ac.uk |date=2012-12-03 |accessdate=2015-04-01}}</ref>

