'''Güven Sazak''' (1935 in [[Ankara]], [[Turkey]] &ndash; 25 April 2011) was the 40th [[President]] of [[Turkcell Super League|Türkiye Süper Ligi]] club [[Fenerbahçe SK]] between 1993 and 1994.<ref>[http://www.fenerbahce.org/kurumsaldetay.asp?ContentID=18 Past Presidents]</ref> He has been a member of the club since 1958.<ref>[[:tr:Güven Sazak|Profil on vikipedi]]</ref>

He was also a member of the [[Fenerbahçe SK]] Board in 1974–75, 1978–80 and 1982–83 Boards.<ref>[http://www.kimkimdir.gen.tr/kimkimdir.php?id=1399 Biography on kimkimdir.com]</ref>

Güven Sazak is the brother of [[Gün Sazak]] (1932–1980), a nationalist politician and former Minister of Customs and Monopolies, who was assassinated by leftist militants.<ref name="kh"/> His other brother, Yılmaz Sazak, served as the President of the [[Turkey Athletic Federation]].<ref name="ntv1"/>

