{{Infobox person | name = Hayden Kho Jr. | image = Dr. Hayden Kho photo by Raymund Isaac.jpg | imagesize = | caption = Hayden Kho at the mall in 2014 | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1980|5|20|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Manila]], [[Philippines]] | occupation = {{hlist|Cosmetic surgeon|Actor|Model|Entrepreneur|Public Speaker}} | spouse = Vicki Belo | children = 1 | birth_name = | othername = Doc Hayden }}
'''Hayden Kho Jr.''' (born May 20, 1980) is a [[Filipinos|Filipino]] cosmetic doctor, entrepreneur, actor and model.
==Biography==
At the age of 16, Kho started his career in ramp [[Model (person)|modeling]] while pursuing a degree in [[medical technology]]. This stint brought him to places like New York City, Singapore, Korea and Japan. Following the footsteps of his father, Hayden Kho, Sr, he earned his degree in Medicine and Surgery from the [[University of Santo Tomas]]. He completed his internship at the [[Makati Medical Center]] where he held the position of President of the Medical Interns. Kho also completed his training in anti-aging medicine through the European Anti-Aging Medicine Society (Paris). In Manila, Kho practiced specific cosmetic dermatology and surgery procedures under the organization of the Belo Medical Group, owned by [[Vicki Belo]].{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}
In 2007, Kho started appearing on Philippine national television as an actor. His career in show business was interrupted when it was reported that Kho had tried to commit suicide in December 2008. In 2009, sex videos of himself with other local and foreign celebrities were distributed over the internet without his knowledge and consent. Shortly thereafter, Kho was brought to a senate hearing and was tried publicly on national television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/video/42403/24oras/hayden-kho-katrina-halili-attend-senate-hearing|title=Hayden Kho, Katrina Halili attend Senate hearing|work=gmanetwork.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> This saga lasted for years and resulted to criminal and civil cases filed against Kho by one of the involved parties, Filipina actress [[Katrina Halili]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bell|first1=Thomas|title=Philippines gripped by actress's affair with Doctor Hunk|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/philippines/5400332/Philippines-gripped-by-actresss-affair-with-Doctor-Hunk.html|work=The Telegraph|date=28 May 2009}}</ref> [[CNN]] tagged this controversy as the most controversial sex scandal in [[Asia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://travel.cnn.com/explorations/none/sex-scandals-asia-139410|title=Asia's top 5 celebrity sex scandals - CNN Travel|work=cnn.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> The Philippine Board of Medicine revoked Kho's license to practice medicine and cited unethical behavior as the basis for his expulsion from the medical society.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interaksyon.com/entertainment/hayden-kho-loses-appeal-to-regain-medical-license/|title=Hayden Kho loses medical license for good|work=interaksyon.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> In December of the same year, Kho tried to commit suicide for the second time.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}.
In 2011, Kho launched his own eponymous brand of fragrances called, "HAYDEN".<ref>http://www.pep.ph/news/27171/Hayden-Kho-launches-perfume-business-in-grand-style</ref> He was tapped as the endorser of the Filipino fashion brand MALDITA MAN <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eQl5qgpwlSM|title=MALDITA MAN Ad Campaign 2012|first=|last=MalditaOfficialTV|date=13 September 2012|publisher=|accessdate=17 November 2016|via=YouTube}}</ref> and also by the cosmetic giant Ever Bilena, Inc. He also hosted the defunct Filipino showbiz oriented talk show ''[[Paparazzi (talk show)|Paparazzi]]'',<ref>http://www.pep.ph/news/28390/hayden-kho-jr-seriously-considering-offer-to-co-host-paparazzi</ref> which was aired on [[Associated Broadcasting Company|TV5]]. Kho was also director of the skin care distribution brand ZO Skin Health in the Philippines.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philstar.com/newsmakers/2013/05/30/947790/healthy-beautiful-skin|title=Healthy & beautiful skin is in - Newsmakers, Other STAR Sections, The Philippine Star - philstar.com|work=philstar.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref>
In 2013, Kho met with Christian philosopher and apologist [[Ravi Zacharias]] in a serendipitous event hosted by some leaders of the [[Christ Commission Fellowship]] (CCF) in Manila and later became a devoted [[Christianity|Christian]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philstar.com/sunday-life/2014/05/25/1326835/after-two-suicide-attempts-hayden-kho-finds-meaning-newfound|title=After two suicide attempts, Hayden Kho finds meaning in newfound spirituality|first=Wilson Lee|last=Flores|work=philstar.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> He is being mentored by Zacharias and by the CCF movement founder, Pastor Peter Tan-Chi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lifestyle.inquirer.net/160603/the-new-hayden-kho-jr-im-not-yet-where-i-want-to-be-but-im-no-longer-who-i-used-to-be/comment-page-5?PageSpeed=noscript|title=The new Hayden Kho Jr: I’m not yet where I want to be, but I’m no longer who I used to be|first=Alex Y.|last=Vergara|work=inquirer.net|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref>
In 2014, Kho went to the [https://www.theocca.org Oxford Centre for Christian Apologetics] at the Oxford University to study Christian apologetics, where he met and was tutored by Christian sociologist and author [[Os Guinness]]; scientist, mathematician, and philosopher [[John Lennox]]; theologian and author [[Alister McGrath]]; and anti-Islam polemicist [[Jay Smith (Christian apologist)|Jay Smith]], among others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lifestyle.inquirer.net/165159/vicki-belo-focuses-on-spiritual-growth-hayden-kho-goes-to-oxford-for-divinity-studies|title=Vicki Belo focuses on spiritual growth; Hayden Kho goes to Oxford for divinity studies|first=Maurice|last=Arcache|work=inquirer.net|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref>
While Kho was studying in [[University of Oxford]], the [[Professional Regulation Commission]] reinstated his medical license.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/07/08/14/hayden-kho-doctor-again|title=Hayden Kho is a doctor again|first=ABS-CBN|last=News|work=abs-cbnnews.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> The same year, all cases against Kho were dismissed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/270023/showbiz/appeals-court-clears-hayden-kho-in-sex-video-case|title=Appeals court clears Hayden Kho in 'sex video' case|work=gmanetwork.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> Kho and Halili reconciled thereafter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/04/30/15/look-hayden-kho-katrina-halili-reconcile|title=LOOK: Hayden Kho, Katrina Halili reconcile|first=ABS-CBN|last=News|work=abs-cbn.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> With respect to his conversion to Christianity, Kho confirmed that he had been practicing faith-based [[sexual abstinence|abstinence]].<ref name="auto"/> It has been reported that Vicki Belo and Hayden Kho conceived their first child, Scarlet Snow Belo, via In Vitro Fertilization (IVF) who was born on March 3, 2015 through surrogacy with an American-Mexican female.<ref>The story behind Dr. Vicki Belo and Hayden Kho's biological child Startattle.com May 22, 2016. Cite web|url=http://www.startattle.com/2016/05/the-story-behind-dr-vicki-belo-and.html?m=1</ref>
Kho resumed his medical practice in 2016 at the now-defunct Sexy Solutions clinics. He owns and runs a real estate website called ZoneListing, Inc.<ref>https://www.zonelisting.com.ph</ref> He is also invested in various software companies that create apps such as Pocket Market and Paylance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loud-panda.com|title=Loud Panda Interactive|work=loud-panda.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref>. Currently, Kho sits in the board of a non-profit organization called "Right Start <ref>http://rightstart.ph</ref>. He also leads the product and services development department of the Belo Medical Group.
