'''Jimmy Lahoud''' (born June 1949)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/NrWDRHiZy25uaapqsmh98Uil7TQ/appointments|title=Jimmy LAHOUD - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House)|author=|date=|website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk|accessdate=25 January 2018}}</ref> is a [[Lebanese people|Lebanese]] businessman and [[restaurateur]] in [[London]], [[England]]. He has owned restaurants such as [[Quo Vadis (restaurant)|Quo Vadis]], [[L'Escargot (restaurant)|L'Escargot]], and Café St. Pierre (which became [[Maison Novelli]]).<ref name="White2008">{{cite book|last=White|first=Marco Pierre|title=The Devil in the Kitchen: Sex, Pain, Madness, and the Making of a Great Chef|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VJOb898jMeYC&pg=PA99|accessdate=28 November 2012|date=27 May 2008|publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing USA|isbn=978-1-59691-497-1|pages=99–}}</ref>  Lahoud is an [[private collection|art collector]], displaying his [[Picasso]], [[Joan Miró|Miró]], [[Chagall]], [[Warhol]] and [[Matisse]] pieces in at least one of his restaurants.<ref name="Gwilliam2011">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/promotions/best-deals-of-the-day/8371839/Sohos-French-fancy-LEscargot-reinvents-the-snail.html|title=Soho's French fancy: L'Escargot reinvents the snail|last=Gwilliam|first=Katy |date=March 9, 2011|publisher=''The Telegraph''|accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref> Lahoud is credited for launching the career of [[celebrity chef]] [[Marco Pierre White]].<ref name="Mathiason">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/eating-out-is-the-new-rock-n-roll-1109861.html|title=Eating out is the new rock 'n' roll |last=Mathiason|first=Nick |date=August 1, 1999|publisher=''The Independent''|accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref> With White, Lahoud established White Star Line Ltd,<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.caterersearch.com/Articles/2006/09/21/308890/marco-pierre-white-profile-ranked-46-in-the-caterersearch100-in-2006.html | title = Marco Pierre White Profile | date = September 2006 | work=Caterer & Hotelkeeper | location = London }}</ref> which owns the [[Belvedere Restaurant]].<ref>[http://www.whitestarline.org.uk/ White Star Line].</ref>

