{{Infobox company | name = Softwear Automation Inc. | logo = | type = | industry = Textile [[Robot]]s | fate = | predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = --> | successor = <!-- or: | successors = --> | founded = <!-- if known: {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} in [[city]], state, country --> | founder = <!-- or: | founders = --> | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | hq_location_city = | hq_location_country = [[United States]] | area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = --> | key_people = CEO - Palaniswamy "Raj" Rajan | products = Bots | owner = <!-- or: | owners = --> | num_employees = | num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) --> | parent = | website = http://softwearautomation.com/ }}
'''Softwear''' or '''Softwear Automation Inc.''' is a United States-based company<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/pamdanziger/2018/02/24/apparel-factory-automation-is-the-only-cure-for-what-ails-fashion-retail/#152cad61336b|title=SoftWear Automation Has A Cure For What Ails Fashion Retail|first=Pamela N.|last=Danziger|publisher=}}</ref> which develops "bots" that can perform advanced sewing in the [[Textile manufacturing|textile industry]]. In [[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]] a $20 million factory is in development with 330 bots becoming fully operational. The cost of each machine-developed t-shirt is estimated to be roughly $0.33 as the factory output is expected to be 23 million shirts per year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-08-30/china-snaps-up-america-s-cheap-robot-labor|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=www.bloomberg.com}}</ref>
